context:
KR:
&lt;안 자는 거야, 파우스트 씨?&gt;
EN:
&lt;Are you still awake, Ms. Faust?&gt;

KR:
&lt;고생하네.&gt;
EN:
&lt;You’re working hard.&gt;

KR:
&lt;아… 이거?&gt;
EN:
&lt;Oh… This thing?&gt;

KR:
&lt;별거는 아니고… 필요했던 기능이 들어온 것 같아서.&gt;
EN:
&lt;It’s nothing much, I was just… making the most of this new feature I’ve needed.&gt;

KR:
&lt;없었어. 놀랍지만.&gt;
EN:
&lt;It didn’t, surprisingly enough.&gt;

KR:
&lt;…몰랐어? 파우스트, 너는 모든걸 아는 줄 알았는데.&gt;
EN:
&lt;…You didn’t know that? I thought you were omniscient, Faust.&gt;

KR:
&lt;너희들 기준에서는 일상적인 단어일지 몰라도…&gt;
EN:
&lt;It might be common vocabulary for you all, but not me…&gt;

KR:
&lt;맞아. 그래서 웬만한 건 전부 적어 놓고 싶어.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Yep. So I wanna write down most stuff here.&gt;

KR:
&lt;그리고 예전부터 종이에 끄적이던 것도 틈틈이 옮겨둬보려고…&gt;
EN:
&lt;And copy down the things I’ve been scribbling on paper while I’m at it…&gt;
